HEADWORD: parimutuel
<hw>par`i*mu"tu*el</hw>
<pr>(p⟦acr⟧r`⟦icr⟧*m⟦umac⟧"ch⟦oomac⟧*⟦ucr⟧l)</pr>, <pos>n.</pos> <def>A
form of betting where winners share the total amount wagered, in
proporation to their bets, and less a portion for the management; --
used commonly in betting at horse racing track. In <ex>parimutuel</ex>
betting, the payoff for a bet does not have fixed odds, but depends on
the amount bet on each outcome.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>WordNet 1.5</source> <source>+PJC</source>]</p>

